# Admin form table layout

Use **`AdminFormTable`** (`$lib/components/admin/AdminFormTable.svelte`) for admin settings and CRUD forms. Do not use `grid`/`form-control` stacks for multi-field admin forms.

## Grid

Fixed **4 columns**: `label | field | label | field`

- One field pair = 2 cells (label + field). Never `colspan="2"` on a single field.
- Full-width field: label in col 1, field `colspan="3"`.
- Action button in second pair: empty col 3 (`aria-hidden="true"`), control in col 4 (e.g. Sort order row → Add category under Slug).
- Checkbox in second pair: empty `colspan="2"` on cols 1–2, label col 3, checkbox col 4.

## Cell classes

- Label: `td.align-middle.p-0` + `label.py-0`
- Field: `td.min-w-0.p-0` + input `w-full`
- Table wrapper: `w-full table-fixed`; form/section: `w-full min-w-0`

## Row order (document forms)

Title+Slug → Category+Parent → Tags+Published → Excerpt (full width). Document sort order is managed on the dashboard via drag-and-drop.

